{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778975755730,"sessionID":"ses_1ccd7dd61ffepBfm6K05Htdrlc","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_EhpYN9ZvDXZfqQ17flyKFJOg","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+Updated GO:0102177 as requested: the term now uses the EC-aligned label, RHEA:58868 reaction definition/xref, MetaCyc:RXN-19724, and the EC:1.14.18.- parent GO:0016716.\n+\n+Validation passed with `make travis_build`. Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n*** Add File: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+## Summary\n+\n+Updated `GO:0102177` to align the term with EC:1.14.18.11 and the full RHEA reaction requested in issue #31985.\n+\n+Changes made:\n+\n+- Renamed the term from `24-methylenelophenol methyl oxidase activity` to `4alpha-monomethylsterol monooxygenase activity`.\n+- Replaced the definition reaction with the RHEA:58868 cytochrome-b5-dependent reaction.\n+- Removed `GOC:pz` from the definition provenance, leaving `PMID:11707264` and `RHEA:58868`.\n+- Changed the RHEA xref from `RHEA:58872` to `RHEA:58868` as an exact match.\n+- Changed the MetaCyc xref from `MetaCyc:RXN-11930` to `MetaCyc:RXN-19724`.\n+- Changed the asserted parent from `GO:0016709` to `GO:0016716`, matching the EC:1.14.18.- parent class.\n+\n+## Rationale\n+\n+The previous GO term described the partial RHEA reaction `RHEA:58872`, while the EC mapping `EC:1.14.18.11` corresponds to plant 4alpha-monomethylsterol monooxygenase and the full reaction represented by `RHEA:58868`. Updating the label, definition, RHEA xref, MetaCyc xref, and parent keeps the molecular function term internally consistent with its EC and RHEA mappings.\n+\n+The existing PMID was checked with `linkml-reference-validator cache reference PMID:11707264`; it resolves to Darnet, Bard, and Rahier 2001, \"Functional identification of sterol-4alpha-methyl oxidase cDNAs from Arabidopsis thaliana by complementation of a yeast erg25 mutant lacking sterol-4alpha-methyl oxidation.\"\n+\n+## Validation\n+\n+- Baseline validation before edits: `make travis_build` passed.\n+- Post-edit validation: `make travis_build` passed.\n+- External ID checks performed:\n+- `runoak -i sqlite:obo:rhea info RHEA:58868 RHEA:58872`\n+- `runoak -i sqlite:obo:eccode info EC:1.14.18.11 EC:1.14.18.-`\n+\n+## Checklist\n+\n+- [x] PLAN: issue context reviewed and requested edits were clear.\n+- [x] PRE-VALIDATION: current ontology validated before changes.\n+- [x] RESEARCH: existing PMID was validated; no new literature references were introduced.\n+- [x] TERM-SEARCH: current GO term, requested parent, and related mapping IDs were checked.\n+- [x] DESIGN-PATTERNS: reaction/mapping guidance consulted; no logical definition or intersection_of edits were needed.\n+- [x] SPECIALIZED-EDITS: reaction, mapping, chemical-entity, and design-pattern guidance consulted as applicable.\n+- [x] EDITS: GO checkout/checkin workflow used for `GO:0102177`.\n+- [x] RELATIONSHIPS: parent updated to `GO:0016716` to match EC:1.14.18.-.\n+- [x] METADATA: no new term metadata needed; existing term tracker retained.\n+- [x] AUTOMATED-VALIDATION: `make travis_build` passed after changes.\n+- [x] REFERENCE-VALIDATION: `PMID:11707264` validated; no hallucinated references added.\n+- [x] CHANGES-COMMITTED: committed locally as `7248fcd Update GO:0102177 reaction mapping`.\n*** End Patch"},"output":"Success. Updated the following files:\nA ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\nA PR_COMMENTS.md","metadata":{"diff":"Index: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/ISSUE_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,3 @@\n+Updated GO:0102177 as requested: the term now uses the EC-aligned label, RHEA:58868 reaction definition/xref, MetaCyc:RXN-19724, and the EC:1.14.18.- parent GO:0016716.\n+\n+Validation passed with `make travis_build`. Changes committed in PR #<NN>.\n\nIndex: /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n===================================================================\n--- /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n+++ /__w/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/PR_COMMENTS.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,41 @@\n+## Summary\n+\n+Updated `GO:0102177` to align the term with EC:1.14.18.11 and the full RHEA reaction requested in issue #31985.\n+\n+Changes made:\n+\n+- Renamed the term from `24-methylenelophenol methyl oxidase activity` to `4alpha-monomethylsterol monooxygenase activity`.\n+- Replaced the definition reaction with the RHEA:58868 cytochrome-b5-dependent reaction.\n+- Removed `GOC:pz` from the definition provenance, leaving `PMID:11707264` and `RHEA:58868`.\n+- Changed the RHEA xref from `RHEA:58872` to `RHEA:58868` as an exact match.\n+- Changed the MetaCyc xref from `MetaCyc:RXN-11930` to `MetaCyc:RXN-19724`.\n+- Changed the asserted parent from `GO:0016709` to `GO:0016716`, matching the EC:1.14.18.- parent class.\n+\n+## Rationale\n+\n+The previous GO term described the partial RHEA reaction `RHEA:58872`, while the EC mapping `EC:1.14.18.11` corresponds to plant 4alpha-monomethylsterol monooxygenase and the full reaction represented by `RHEA:58868`. Updating the label, definition, RHEA xref, MetaCyc xref, and parent keeps the molecular function term internally consistent with its EC and RHEA mappings.\n+\n+The existing PMID was checked with `linkml-reference-validator cache reference PMID:11707264`; it resolves to Darnet, Bard, and Rahier 2001, \"Functional identification of sterol-4alpha-methyl oxidase cDNAs from Arabidopsis thaliana by complementation of a yeast erg25 mutant lacking sterol-4alpha-methyl oxidation.\"\n+\n+## Validation\n+\n+- Baseline validation before edits: `make travis_build` passed.\n+- Post-edit validation: `make travis_build` passed.\n+- External ID checks performed